5. **Care and monitoring:** Regularly check the growth of the mushrooms to ensure the right moisture and temperature, and make sure they are not exposed to harmful fungi or insects.

6. **Harvesting:** When the mushrooms are ready, you can gently harvest them using scissors or your hands.

It is important to be knowledgeable about identifying edible mushrooms if you are trying to grow wild varieties. If you are unsure, consult an expert to ensure your safety.
